<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-5F1A8914-583D-428B-9851-DCEC19B052D9" version="1" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-5F1A8914-583D-428B-9851-DCEC19B052D9" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title "> How to interpreted the Demo print</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-FCCCBBA1-3996-4617-83C0-E78C1A39AB95" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> CMYK demo print gloss/matte</title><fig id="GUID-DAE2FEF3-E862-47A3-8A29-ED65CBD6DCDF" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-90819685-972F-44F7-A2BA-218EE0B8E3B8-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-90819685-972F-44F7-A2BA-218EE0B8E3B8-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">At the top left side a table is printed with information like: 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Serial number of the system 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Date/time printed 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Print mode 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p ">Multiple different media profile settings used 
</p></li></ul><table id="GUID-0E8E425D-E2FB-417D-BE55-B2DEFD126324" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="3" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="10*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="30*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col3" colnum="3" colwidth="60*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Area 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Information 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Image 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">1 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> This area contains squares for each color except white. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Each color square is buildup of squares ranging from 5% ink to 100% ink coverage 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Purpose and What to look for: 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The patches might not show any artifacts. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-A4A9019F-A037-4B23-97C8-7377C60F6257" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7C668E6C-8964-4648-861C-BB76149C1CEB-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7C668E6C-8964-4648-861C-BB76149C1CEB-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">2 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">This area contains so called "Trapping boxes" 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> All combinations of color are there, except white 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> These trapping boxes are a quick scan for Uni/ Bidirectional and X-direction (miss-) alignments of printheads in the machine 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> At 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">a</b> and 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">a'</b>, which is the carriage direction (Fast scan); there should be a white space visible between colors, no need for an even distance. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This is affected by the Uni/ bi directional alignment. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> At 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">b</b> and 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">b'</b>, which is the media step direction; there should be a white space visible between colors, no need for an even distance. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> If this is not, the printhead mounting should be verified. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> All trapping boxes should be checked for both directions. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-4476F6DA-CC4D-4A1F-A19C-1D20366880F4" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-31119070-DA05-4F25-BD69-29CDEE1CB795-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-31119070-DA05-4F25-BD69-29CDEE1CB795-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> This area is printed with single color black (<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">K</b>) 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The 6 pt. text should be clearly readable. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-47E94082-ACDE-4E3A-A50A-B200AD2D8DE6" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9E29D573-5865-4813-83E4-01055A1E3DA4-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9E29D573-5865-4813-83E4-01055A1E3DA4-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3a 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> This area is printed with 4 colors (<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">CMYK)</b> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The 8 pt. text should be clearly readable. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-38108A09-C9C2-45F0-97E1-9E69341C39E2" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-DAC76347-75CC-424A-B378-B0C3CB09DC81-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-DAC76347-75CC-424A-B378-B0C3CB09DC81-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">3b 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> This area is printed with 4 colors (<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">CMYK)</b> but as a knockout 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The 10 pt. text should be clearly readable. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-B1C2F6A0-27D6-4E79-BFC1-302EA52FDB1D" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-71F4C1BE-982D-4940-A958-5C8E9BB89662-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-71F4C1BE-982D-4940-A958-5C8E9BB89662-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">4 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p "> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This area is for checking 
<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">uniformity, consistency</i> 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> It contains a dark blue sky and medium dark halftones. 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-B913ADAF-7BDF-4E0F-9BB4-ACABF019BACD" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-EDC6DF4E-A187-457D-9E14-23815E8294B0-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-EDC6DF4E-A187-457D-9E14-23815E8294B0-low.png"/></fig></entry></row><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">5 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">This area is split up in an upper non-color managed part and a lower color managed part The middle black bar (5b) is composite black created with all 4 colors. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> This area contains bars in CMY, K, Green and Blue. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The 4k area is printed with C, M, Y and K and is completely non-color managed. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The Green area is printed with C and Y 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The Blue area is printed with C and M 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The Red area is printed with Y and M 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> Area 5 is for checking:<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">banding</i> in solids (gloss and density)<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">lines</i> 
</p></entry><entry colname="col3" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-F98E83C2-C9B6-4E5E-BC4B-540BAD6F40FD" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-FDA7AE61-43CC-44A9-AF6F-8B587823ED82-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-FDA7AE61-43CC-44A9-AF6F-8B587823ED82-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-B49AEAE7-42CD-4D08-9FBB-54648A1670F9" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> FLXfinish+ demo print gloss/matte</title><p class="- topic/p "> No legend is printed for the FLXfinish+ as all media-related settings are printed during the first print.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The spit bar on the right side is a normal function to keep all nozzles in optimal condition.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> The bar may not need to be visually evaluated.
</p><fig id="GUID-CA0562EF-ADC6-4CFB-86E5-AE9FF72D36DC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-7769A151-BAEB-4992-9C77-6629C70F8811-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-7769A151-BAEB-4992-9C77-6629C70F8811-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">No white lines between the gloss and matte squares should be visible.
</p><fig id="GUID-03E425A8-A3DF-40B4-A884-2284D946E072" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-61D9F031-346D-49E4-8EF6-2FA766D99CD9-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-61D9F031-346D-49E4-8EF6-2FA766D99CD9-low.png"/></fig><fig id="GUID-81ACF41B-3328-484F-99F4-D3501B3FEA53" class="- topic/fig "/><p class="- topic/p "> White lines visible in y-direction might not occur.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In case white lines are visible in x-direction: verification on recent media calibration.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> In case of gloss banding, the mirrors need to be re-adjusted.
</p></section><section id="GUID-AD27B9C8-6F3C-4E22-8F69-45640CCFED52" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> White demo print</title><fig id="GUID-B10E6F8E-922C-44E5-BBCD-DA34F3881191" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-266FA276-2ECF-4624-85BD-5FADCEEB385D-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-266FA276-2ECF-4624-85BD-5FADCEEB385D-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The print has been printed using white specialty ink as a three-layer print. When printed onto transparent media, the facial image is visible from both sides, as demonstrated in the example below.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The spitting bar on the right-hand side is a normal function designed to keep all nozzles in working condition. The bar does not need to be visually evaluated.
</p><fig id="GUID-79B72D34-2878-4210-A326-3EA10230421B" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-1AF9CE58-98EF-4C6D-8767-C6774EC3F5E4-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-1AF9CE58-98EF-4C6D-8767-C6774EC3F5E4-low.png"/></fig><p class="- topic/p ">The image contains light halftones, light blue’s and very fine detail in the skin and the eyes.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">It should look very natural when printed.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">No artifacts might be visible.
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-EF42FFF3-C6AF-4939-AE5C-9EB2061E0E1B.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Image Quality</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
</task>